I admit that I am not a huge fan of the `poll` interface. We support it because that is how the java client works, but I think using the iterator is much more pythonic. Perhaps something like:
```
consumer = KafkaConsumer(...., consumer_timeout_ms=1000)
while True:
    for message in consumer:
        print(message)
        if self.stop_event.is_set():
            break
````

